{
  "stem": "20142.4",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Not that the Germans were so gracious to give us half a day, but they needed some rest for themself, too.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And so they did not force us to work on half a day on Sunday.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The only free time that we had was between Sunday 12 o'clock until the evening.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And you were sitting outside, and there were all kind of things to be conducted, like shaving, or sharing, barber was active.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And of course, if he didn't like your face, he was shaving you with a razor that was very dull.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But if he did like you, then he sharpened the razor.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There was no soap, or anything like that, to wash yourself with, and things like this.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The only soap that I remember was given to us when we went to [INAUDIBLE], and there was maybe once in a month.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The funny part of it was on the soap was written R-I-S, which we were translating it as [SPEAKING YIDDISH], pure Jewish soap.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Whether that was true or not, I-- we could not tell.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But it was the substance of [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] very sandy without any true value of a soap.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But somehow, we managed to wash yourself [INAUDIBLE] leave that we had during this hot days and some cold days.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It is very hard to describe to people what it means not to be able to take a shower, never mind every day, but at least once a week.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "How can a human being survive?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, we did survive somehow.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we overcame this situation with hygiene, and we're very fortunate.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It is not easy to describe what food we had.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We had a small piece of bread and a little bit of coffee in the morning.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
